---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="Demos — Andy Rogers" description="Interactive learning samples by Andy Rogers.">
  <div class="container">
    <section class="hero">
      <h1>Demos</h1>
      <p class="tagline">Interactive samples of AESurvey Studio &mdash; my open-source toolkit for Actionable Experience Surveys.</p>
      <div class="prose">
        <p>
          <strong>Actionable Experience Surveys (AES)</strong> are a survey method I designed to replace flat
          &ldquo;lovely&rdquo; satisfaction scores with feedback you can actually act on. Every question uses an
          unbiased prompt, four or more real-sentence answer options, and a mapping to bands
          (Alarming &rarr; Concerning &rarr; Acceptable &rarr; Superior). The result is a headline number and a
          specific to-do list, from the same question.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>AESurvey Studio</strong> is the small open-source toolkit that makes AES easy to run:
          a builder, a browser-based take page, and a report analyser. Everything runs client-side &mdash; no
          server, no login, no data touching anyone else&rsquo;s infrastructure.
        </p>
        <p class="reads">
          Full write-ups on the Lab:
          <a href="https://lab.andyrogers.design/p/actionable-experience-surveys">Why the method exists &rarr;</a>
          &middot;
          <a href="https://lab.andyrogers.design/p/aesurvey-studio">Why I built the tool &rarr;</a>
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>1. Explore a report</h2>
      <p>Click <em>Load sample data</em> below to see what a completed AES report looks like &mdash; twelve
        respondents across four questions. Hover any band segment for the statement respondents
        picked, and expand a question&rsquo;s comments to read what they said. Or drop in your own
        response files.</p>
      <iframe class="demo-frame" src="/demos/aes-report/index.html" title="AES Report" loading="lazy"></iframe>
      <p><a href="/demos/aes-report/index.html">Open the report full screen &rarr;</a></p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>2. Build your own survey</h2>
      <p>Write the questions, tag each statement to a band, and get a shareable link. Send that
        link to your respondents &mdash; they take the survey in their browser and email you their
        responses, or copy a link that opens the report above with their single answer pre-loaded.
        No server, no login, no data on anyone else&rsquo;s infrastructure.</p>
      <p>
        <a class="btn-link" href="/demos/aes-builder/index.html">Open the survey builder &rarr;</a>
      </p>
      <p class="small-note">Click <em>Load demo</em> inside the builder to see how the example above is put together.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>3. Deploy in your own LMS</h2>
      <p>A ready-to-upload example AES survey &mdash; a short post-workshop reflection on giving effective
        feedback. It records each respondent&rsquo;s band, the exact statement they picked, and any
        free-text comment as SCORM interactions, so you can export the responses (as a Track-details
        CSV from Totara, or the equivalent from any modern LMS) and drop them into the report above.</p>
      <div class="demo-downloads">
        <p class="demo-downloads-head">Download the SCORM package</p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <a href="/demos/aes-survey/downloads/aes-demo-feedback-scorm2004.zip" download>SCORM 2004 (.zip)</a>
            <span class="demo-downloads-note"> &mdash; for most modern LMSs (Totara, Moodle, SCORM Cloud, etc.)</span>
          </li>
          <li>
            <a href="/demos/aes-survey/downloads/aes-demo-feedback-scorm12.zip" download>SCORM 1.2 (.zip)</a>
            <span class="demo-downloads-note"> &mdash; for older LMSs that don&rsquo;t support 2004</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="demo-author">
      <h2>Under the hood</h2>
      <p>
        AESurvey Studio is open source under an MIT licence. The builder above is the current
        authoring surface; the SCORM engine, the response model, and the analyser are all in the
        repo, ready to be adapted or integrated into your own tooling.
      </p>
      <p>
        <a href="https://github.com/andyrogersdesign/aesurveys">View on GitHub &rarr;</a>
      </p>
    </section>
  </div>
</Base>
